               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1171" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1171" type="surname" value="HORNE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1171" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HORNE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a silversmith. On the 6th of June the prisoner came and offered me a broken silver spoon for sale—I asked her where she got it—she said, "My mistress gave it me for my day's wages"—I asked who her mistress was—she said, "That is my business, not yours"—I sent my young man for a policeman, and she walked out, but before that she said, "If you won't buy it give it me back"—I said, "No, you wait"—my young man brought the policeman, and he took her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1172" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1172" type="surname" value="MUMFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1172" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE MUMFORD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 207.) I took the prisoner—she said she took the spoon from her mistress's premises, in Jubilee-place—I went there, and saw her mistress.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I said I would show him where it was; the Magistrate dis<lb></lb>missed the case.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1173" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1173" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1173" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1173" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow, and live in Jubilee-place. The prisoner worked as a charwoman for my daughter—I have known her nearly four years—she left my house on the 6th of June, and was brought back in about half an hour—this spoon is my daughter's, Margaret Watson—her husband's name is Thomas—they live in the same house with me—I had not given the spoon to the prisoner for wages—it was not broken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I accidentally broke it; I sat down with it in my pocket.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
